class Solution {
    public long minimumSteps(String s) {
        long steps = 0;
        int blackBalls = 0;
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (c == '1') {
                blackBalls++;
            } else {
                steps += blackBalls;
            }
        }
        return steps;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the string once, maintaining a count of black balls encountered so far. For each white ball, it adds the current count of black balls to the total steps, effectively calculating the minimum swaps needed to move all black balls to the right.

